"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by the British Pharmacological Society (WSC050)&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBPS is the primary UK learned society concerned with research into drugs and the way they work. Our members work in a\ncademia, industry, and the health services, and many are medically qualified. The Society covers the whole spectrum of pharmacology, including laboratory, clinical, toxicological and regulatory aspects. \nClinic\nal pharmacology is the medical speciality\n dedi\ncated to promoting safe and effective use of medicines for patient benefit. Clinical pharmacologists work as consultants in the NHS and many hold prominent positions in UK Universities.\n&#xa0;\nNo interests to declare.\n \n&#xa0;\nAugust 2013\n&#xa0;\n \nhttp://sciencecampaign.org.uk/?p=12860\n \nhttp://www.pnas.org/content/early/2012/09/14/1211286109.abstract\n \nhttp://www.hesa.ac.uk/content/view/1905/251/, table 12\n \nhttp://www.hesa.ac.uk/content/view/1906/251/, table 2a\n \nHESA statistics 2006/7 (purchased content)\n \nHESA statistics 2006/7 (purchased content)\n"